[1] Syria (Aleppo): outbreak, alert
Date: Thu 19 Jan 2022 12:15 EET
Source: Enabbaladi [in Arabic, trans., edited]
https://www.enabbaladi.net/archives/540831


Measles, Syria (Aleppo), clusters
---------------------------------
In a statement dated 15 Jan 2022, the "Syrian Interim Government" warned of an outbreak of the disease in northwestern Syria, announcing the 1st death of measles in Afrin, a 12-year-old girl.

The statement confirmed the discovery of 30 cases of the disease in the Al-Bab region, and more than one in Afrin, the majority of which were children under 5 years old, in addition to the suspected presence of congenital rubella syndrome in a newborn girl, during the period from December 2021 to 7 Jan 2022.

The Minister of Health in the "interim government," Dr Maram al-Sheikh, said in an interview with Enab Baladi that, until now, it was not known why 2 clusters of infections appeared in 2 specific areas (Al-Bab and Afrin).

Al-Sheikh added that every year, several cases of the disease were recorded, but they were with mild symptoms, and in separate areas, so they did not pose a danger from a public health perspective.

Al-Sheikh believes that the reason for the spread is the emergence of a mutation in the causative virus, which led to the emergence of a new strain, or the failure of some people to adhere to the vaccine, or to forget some doses.

The overall turnout for routine vaccinations was excellent in previous periods, and deaths from measles were only recorded in rare cases, such as what happened this year [2022], according to Al-Sheikh.

He added that the vaccine is routine, and people accept it, but there are complex reasons for the possibility of new infections, and this happens annually, but with light and scattered injuries, and he called on people not to be afraid.

Minister Al-Sheikh explained that the reason for warning of any contagious epidemic that is supposed to be one of the diseases controlled by vaccines, is the emergence of any cluster, or the occurrence of death among those cases.

Investigations are carried out on the presence of mutations, focus on monitoring this epidemic within the community, and conducting a vaccination campaign in addition to routine vaccination, so that the matter is contained from its beginning before it turns into an epidemic.

The Ministry of Health in the "interim government" contacted the vaccination teams to start a campaign to vaccinate all children against measles, according to Al-Sheikh.

The risk of measles spreading in Syria
More than 30 000 suspected cases have been reported in opposition-held areas, according to the BioMed Central report .

